         <abstract>
            <p>Within an investment management organization there is often a definite sequence in which potential users participate in the flow of new investment information. Many factors contribute to differences among portfolio managers' position in the sequence, including differences in their ability, their account loads and the kind of competitive pressures they face. Disclosure to the SEC of the sequence of participation would be painful for many institutions, simply because rules might be necessary on matters they have treated loosely and informally in the past.</p>
          </abstract>
